name: A Whitman Kind of Whim Pic O'day #900
description:
7X7" high res iPhoneography image printed on archival paper and mounted on an artist-signed black foam core, ready to slip in to a frame or hang directly on the wall. From my daily visual diary Facebook 'Pic O'day' Project (or other album, as titled).

Pic O'day #900

A Whitman Kind of Whim

Coming up soon and for the last couple of years I do what Walt said to do and '...read these leaves in the open air', my favorite of his passages. 
It's the one that starts out, "This is what you shall do: love the earth and sun, and animals, despise riches, give alms to everyone that asks.." and so on and so forth about several more things that I naturally align with.
I never did know what the title 'Leaves of Grass' actually signified until I looked it up recently on a whim, which endeared it and Walt to me even more.
But even better was my discovery that my new favorite show, Breaking Bad, is chock full of Whitman references and homages.

So as we're only on season 2, and the holiday season approaches it looks to be a Whitman kind of Winter coming up, yo.
Actually Jessie probably would've ended that sentence with a "bitch!" too.. 

Dang, we love that show.

Nov 2012

description:
7X7" high res iPhoneography image printed on archival paper and mounted on an artist-signed black foam core, ready to slip in to a frame or hang directly on the wall. From my daily visual diary Facebook 'Pic O'day' Project (or other album, as titled).

Pic O'day #465
So that was cool.
Was starting to feel the first small pangs of stress as I got out of the car to head in to a crowded Costco earlier today. I was thinking of the time crunch I'm under, feeling that anxious buzz topped with the weighty feeling of not a lot of money going around.
He caught my eye from atop the neighboring car's antenna. He kept looking at me and I kept looking at him. 
The only time he moved was to hop up in the air and land in a different position to give me another angle to shoot.
I fairly immediately felt the same calm all my nature connections give me and the reminder that all that other stuff is ... just stuff. 
Sept. 8, 2011
